<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

3
00:00:15,051 --> 00:00:18,487
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

4
00:00:18,555 --> 00:00:22,150
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh! Just go my way</i>

5
00:00:22,225 --> 00:00:25,490
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

6
00:00:25,562 --> 00:00:27,496
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>

7
00:00:29,299 --> 00:00:32,234
<i>Down a difficult road</i>
<i>filled with endless struggles</i>

8
00:00:32,302 --> 00:00:36,102
<i>Where do you think you are going</i>
<i>following someone else's map?</i>

9
00:00:36,506 --> 00:00:43,344
<i>An insightful crow comes along</i>
<i>to tear up the map</i>

10
00:00:43,580 --> 00:00:50,645
<i>Now open your eyes and</i>
<i>take a look at the truth (Yeah!)</i>

11
00:00:50,954 --> 00:00:57,086
<i>There's nothing to lose,</i>
<i>so let's GO!!!</i>

12
00:00:57,227 --> 00:01:01,493
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

13
00:01:01,564 --> 00:01:05,159
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

14
00:01:05,235 --> 00:01:08,568
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

15
00:01:08,638 --> 00:01:12,267
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh!</i>
<i>Just go my way</i>

16
00:01:12,342 --> 00:01:15,937
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

17
00:01:16,012 --> 00:01:19,504
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best!</i>

18
00:01:19,582 --> 00:01:23,177
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

19
00:01:23,253 --> 00:01:27,349
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best! BANG!</i>

20
00:01:35,108 --> 00:01:38,202
I've done it!
The water is turning!

21
00:01:38,645 --> 00:01:41,808
It seems it's going to be easier
than I thought to break it.

22
00:01:42,282 --> 00:01:48,448
Then I'll go take a little rest
until it's done... with this.

23
00:01:48,522 --> 00:01:50,786
Hey! What is that?!

24
00:01:51,024 --> 00:01:55,961
I need it to kill the time.
And also to get some sleep.

25
00:01:57,164 --> 00:02:00,600
Huh! The way it's going,
it won't even be an afternoon nap!

26
00:02:01,768 --> 00:02:05,431
Is that so...?
Call me when it is broken.

27
00:02:05,639 --> 00:02:06,901
Just wait!

28
00:02:08,008 --> 00:02:11,808
If it keeps up like this,
I'll learn it within today!

29
00:02:17,618 --> 00:02:23,454
<i>Keep on Training!</i>
<i>Pop Goes the Water Balloon</i>

30
00:02:35,235 --> 00:02:39,763
Oh man! Why doesn't it break!

31
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:43,175
Huh? Are you done with it?

32
00:02:45,846 --> 00:02:50,545
Ah... well, it's almost done
or how should I call it.

33
00:02:50,884 --> 00:02:52,317
Oh boy...

34
00:02:52,786 --> 00:02:56,779
It seems like I went beyond
an afternoon nap and had a deep sleep.

35
00:02:58,292 --> 00:03:01,193
Hey, hey... how do I break it?

36
00:03:04,998 --> 00:03:08,661
Didn't I tell you I can't give
a detailed explanation until it's broken?

37
00:03:11,071 --> 00:03:13,062
All right, I understand...

38
00:03:14,675 --> 00:03:18,076
Naturally, you're supposed to realize it
through trial and error

39
00:03:18,145 --> 00:03:20,909
when mastering a Jutsu, but...

40
00:03:21,114 --> 00:03:22,308
Yeah, yeah.

41
00:03:22,816 --> 00:03:26,479
I guess I'll teach you just
a tiny bit on the Jutsu...

42
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:29,850
You, try rotating the water!

43
00:03:30,090 --> 00:03:31,580
Oh, okay.

44
00:03:38,365 --> 00:03:42,734
Right or left... which direction did you
imagine when you rotate it?

45
00:03:42,903 --> 00:03:46,304
Hmm... well, to the left...

46
00:03:46,773 --> 00:03:48,536
Hey, come over here.

47
00:03:48,809 --> 00:03:49,571
Okay...

48
00:03:55,115 --> 00:03:57,345
Huh, I thought so...

49
00:03:58,652 --> 00:04:00,586
W-What?

50
00:04:00,787 --> 00:04:03,813
You are in fact a right rotation type.

51
00:04:04,558 --> 00:04:05,388
Right?

52
00:04:05,726 --> 00:04:07,284
In order to build up Chakra,

53
00:04:07,361 --> 00:04:10,228
it is necessary to blend the energy...

54
00:04:10,697 --> 00:04:14,656
Chakra
Spiritual energy Physical energy
So everybody unconsciously builds up
Chakra inside the body by rotating it.

55
00:04:15,202 --> 00:04:18,865
Right Left
Whether the rotation at that point
is to the right or to the left

56
00:04:18,939 --> 00:04:20,497
differs in the individual.

57
00:04:20,874 --> 00:04:24,139
Therefore, if you imagine
the rotation of the water balloon

58
00:04:24,211 --> 00:04:27,408
opposite to that of your rotation type
in this training,

59
00:04:27,547 --> 00:04:30,744
your Chakra flow divides and resists

60
00:04:30,817 --> 00:04:33,217
and the momentum of
the rotation does not get on track.

61
00:04:34,154 --> 00:04:38,614
You should be able to figure
that kind of stuff on your own.

62
00:04:38,992 --> 00:04:43,486
But how did you figure out that
I'm a right type so fast?

63
00:04:45,399 --> 00:04:47,196
The cowlick on your head!

64
00:04:47,267 --> 00:04:50,065
It's pretty much determined that you're
a right type if a whorl rolls to the right

65
00:04:50,237 --> 00:04:52,797
and you're a left type
if it rolls to the left.

66
00:04:52,873 --> 00:04:54,500
It's simple.

67
00:04:54,841 --> 00:04:58,004
Huh, so I have a right roll!

68
00:04:58,412 --> 00:05:02,906
Yes, so if you want to rotate it,
you have to imagine a right rotation.

69
00:05:03,016 --> 00:05:06,975
I never really paid attention
that until now...

70
00:05:07,187 --> 00:05:10,452
But this Jutsu is just the one for you.

71
00:05:10,891 --> 00:05:15,624
Hand sign is completely unnecessary.
All you need is Chakra.

72
00:05:15,929 --> 00:05:18,864
There is no need to learn
a finicky hand sign!

73
00:05:19,433 --> 00:05:20,900
It's okay to be stupid!

74
00:05:21,001 --> 00:05:23,026
I'm not stupid!

75
00:05:23,470 --> 00:05:25,904
I'm the man who's eventually going
to become a Hokage!

76
00:05:25,972 --> 00:05:27,371
It's easy once you understand!

77
00:05:27,441 --> 00:05:31,138
This Jutsu, I'll completely master it
if I got three days!

78
00:05:32,979 --> 00:05:34,378
Three days, huh?

79
00:05:35,449 --> 00:05:39,283
This Jutsu is a Ninjutsu
that the Fourth Hokage passed on to us.

80
00:05:39,619 --> 00:05:40,517
Huh?

81
00:05:40,654 --> 00:05:44,920
It took him three whole years
to perfect this Jutsu...

82
00:05:45,225 --> 00:05:46,817
This Jutsu is second from the top

83
00:05:46,893 --> 00:05:49,225
on the six degrees of
difficulty in mastering...

84
00:05:49,429 --> 00:05:52,489
It's an A rank, super high level Ninjutsu.

85
00:05:54,534 --> 00:05:58,300
In order to learn this move,
there are three steps in the training.

86
00:05:59,005 --> 00:06:01,906
This "Water Balloon Breaking"
is the first step.

87
00:06:04,544 --> 00:06:08,378
<i>It took the genius Ninja,</i>
<i>the Fourth Hokage...</i>

88
00:06:09,716 --> 00:06:10,808
<i>Three years...</i>

89
00:06:11,418 --> 00:06:14,717
There's no point in explaining
anymore to someone

90
00:06:14,788 --> 00:06:17,552
who can't even clear the first step.

91
00:06:17,624 --> 00:06:19,922
Do the rest by yourself!

92
00:06:20,393 --> 00:06:23,362
Take care!
I'm going to return to the town.

93
00:06:23,697 --> 00:06:25,756
I have to gather some information...

94
00:06:26,767 --> 00:06:28,234
What will you do?

95
00:06:30,771 --> 00:06:32,966
<i>A rank in degree of difficulty</i>
<i>in mastering...</i>

96
00:06:33,473 --> 00:06:35,941
<i>The Ninjutsu left behind</i>
<i>by the Fourth Hokage...</i>

97
00:06:42,783 --> 00:06:44,648
I'm not gonna go back yet!

98
00:06:46,353 --> 00:06:47,149
Huh...

99
00:06:47,587 --> 00:06:50,078
So long... Don't go overboard with it.

100
00:06:56,263 --> 00:06:59,198
Now, what will happen?

101
00:06:59,666 --> 00:07:01,657
It's something to be concerned about...

102
00:07:01,802 --> 00:07:03,099
Mister!

103
00:07:03,804 --> 00:07:05,362
Why don't you stop by?

104
00:07:05,572 --> 00:07:07,733
This month is our special service month.

105
00:07:07,841 --> 00:07:10,708
Whoa! It's a special service month?

106
00:07:10,777 --> 00:07:12,574
The more you visit,
the more you benefit.

107
00:07:13,180 --> 00:07:14,807
Here you go, a stamp card!

108
00:07:14,948 --> 00:07:16,882
I'll give you lots and lots of service!

109
00:07:18,885 --> 00:07:20,580
I'll come, I'll come!

110
00:07:38,305 --> 00:07:40,000
Hey! Come on down, Shu!

111
00:07:41,808 --> 00:07:44,106
Hey, hey, where is the toilet?

112
00:07:51,484 --> 00:07:54,817
<i>I don't have time to spend three years.</i>

113
00:07:55,522 --> 00:07:57,046
All right now!

114
00:07:57,190 --> 00:08:00,455
Training, once again today!
I'm gonna work hard like a blaze!

115
00:08:06,099 --> 00:08:08,567
Break! Break! Break!

116
00:08:11,872 --> 00:08:13,999
Why won't it break?

117
00:08:23,283 --> 00:08:24,978
Little Jiraiya, you're so naughty!

118
00:08:27,254 --> 00:08:29,484
Men are all naughty!

119
00:08:37,597 --> 00:08:38,928
Dang it!

120
00:08:41,301 --> 00:08:45,260
<i>Three days have passed since</i>
<i>I got the tip from that Pervy Sage...</i>

121
00:08:46,072 --> 00:08:49,303
<i>The rubber is stretched this much,</i>
<i>but why won't it break?</i>

122
00:08:49,809 --> 00:08:52,869
<i>What am I doing different from</i>
<i>that Pervy Sage?</i>

123
00:08:57,684 --> 00:09:00,118
This is great! This is so great!

124
00:09:13,266 --> 00:09:14,233
What the?

125
00:09:20,106 --> 00:09:23,303
Whoa, he stinks of alcohol.

126
00:09:25,946 --> 00:09:27,538
I'm gonna eat now!

127
00:09:29,849 --> 00:09:30,816
Huh?

128
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,144
What's the matter?

129
00:09:39,626 --> 00:09:42,094
Oh dang it!

130
00:09:42,662 --> 00:09:45,096
Darn it! Why is it like this?!

131
00:09:55,375 --> 00:10:00,335
<i>No need to learn a finicky hand sign!</i>
<i>It's okay to be stupid!</i>

132
00:10:01,481 --> 00:10:05,611
<i>He said that there's no need to form</i>
<i>a hand signal, but...</i>

133
00:10:19,733 --> 00:10:23,066
Hey! That's not your toy...

134
00:10:34,714 --> 00:10:35,681
This is it!

135
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:44,586
Hurry up and wake up!
Hey, you Pervy Sage!

136
00:10:46,092 --> 00:10:48,185
Uh... G-Good timing.

137
00:10:48,261 --> 00:10:50,525
Why don't you bring me some water...

138
00:10:50,830 --> 00:10:51,728
Water?

139
00:10:59,606 --> 00:11:02,473
The first step is cleared!

140
00:11:04,745 --> 00:11:05,973
Cleared...?

141
00:11:06,513 --> 00:11:09,004
Well, let's have you show it to me.

142
00:11:09,549 --> 00:11:12,814
All right! Watch it carefully!

143
00:11:17,824 --> 00:11:18,916
<i>Left hand?</i>

144
00:11:31,405 --> 00:11:32,895
Go!

145
00:11:37,210 --> 00:11:40,338
All right! See that?! See that?!

146
00:11:43,684 --> 00:11:45,276
You're sleeping!

147
00:11:47,554 --> 00:11:49,078
Sorry, sorry.

148
00:11:49,256 --> 00:11:52,623
I'm tired from the days and nights
of gathering information.

149
00:11:53,093 --> 00:11:55,527
<i>But that seems suspicious to begin with!</i>

150
00:11:55,762 --> 00:11:57,229
<i>You still stink of alcohol too!</i>

151
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:01,129
<i>Nevertheless...</i>

152
00:12:01,768 --> 00:12:04,760
<i>You rotate the water inside the water balloon</i>
<i>that you hold in your left hand</i>

153
00:12:04,838 --> 00:12:08,137
<i>by repeatedly applying it</i>
<i>with your right hand...</i>

154
00:12:09,009 --> 00:12:10,806
<i>It seems little strange of an idea, but...</i>

155
00:12:10,877 --> 00:12:12,777
<i>You're an interesting kid.</i>

156
00:12:14,748 --> 00:12:20,812
You understood the trick pretty well.
It's all thanks to me, though.

157
00:12:22,756 --> 00:12:25,247
It's thanks to this guy!

158
00:12:26,727 --> 00:12:27,489
Huh?

159
00:12:28,161 --> 00:12:32,257
I realized after I saw this cat playing
with the water balloon.

160
00:12:33,867 --> 00:12:36,392
He kept on flicking it with
his paw many times

161
00:12:36,470 --> 00:12:39,098
and the water inside shocked
in all different kinds of direction...

162
00:12:39,339 --> 00:12:41,307
Then it came to me like "bingo!"

163
00:12:42,342 --> 00:12:44,401
How did it come like bingo?

164
00:12:44,811 --> 00:12:47,939
The time when the Pervy Sage
first showed me breaking it...

165
00:12:48,515 --> 00:12:52,110
I remembered how the water balloon
surface was not smooth.

166
00:12:52,886 --> 00:12:55,616
Until then,
I was always only rotating the water

167
00:12:55,689 --> 00:12:57,623
in the one same direction...

168
00:12:58,358 --> 00:13:01,293
I realized that the Pervy Sage's
water balloon was not smooth

169
00:13:01,361 --> 00:13:05,627
because the water inside was rotating
in different directions.

170
00:13:06,533 --> 00:13:10,469
And after doing it in my own way,
it broke!

171
00:13:11,471 --> 00:13:13,598
<i>It seems it's still not possible for you</i>

172
00:13:13,673 --> 00:13:16,335
<i>to rotate it violently with one hand, but...</i>

173
00:13:16,643 --> 00:13:19,771
<i>I suppose you thought it out</i>
<i>in your own way.</i>

174
00:13:20,947 --> 00:13:22,778
That's just what he expected of me!

175
00:13:23,383 --> 00:13:27,046
Anyhow...
The first step is complete for now.

176
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,781
All right!

177
00:13:28,955 --> 00:13:31,651
Do you want to see it one more time?
One more time!

178
00:13:31,725 --> 00:13:32,692
Oww!

179
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:36,656
<i>You used too much Chakra and</i>
<i>it gradually reached the point</i>

180
00:13:36,730 --> 00:13:38,664
<i>where there's burden</i>
<i>on the Chakra Network...</i>

181
00:13:39,232 --> 00:13:41,826
<i>But the next one won't be like this!</i>

182
00:13:45,539 --> 00:13:49,100
Okay. Now, we will proceed
to the second step.

183
00:13:49,342 --> 00:13:50,274
Yeah!

184
00:13:50,343 --> 00:13:53,574
It seems like we can finally go
into some serious training!

185
00:13:53,647 --> 00:13:54,978
- Here you go
- Huh?

186
00:13:55,849 --> 00:14:00,877
Rubber ball?
Something like this again?!

187
00:14:01,521 --> 00:14:03,352
Now, you'll break this one!

188
00:14:07,594 --> 00:14:10,154
It's one hundred times harder
than the water balloon!

189
00:14:22,042 --> 00:14:22,940
<i>It's hard...</i>

190
00:14:23,944 --> 00:14:27,880
The first step is rotation,
the second step is force.

191
00:14:28,582 --> 00:14:30,140
Since there is no water inside,

192
00:14:30,217 --> 00:14:32,879
it's more difficult to imagine
the rotation of Chakra,

193
00:14:32,953 --> 00:14:35,114
so it becomes more difficult
to rotate the Chakra as well.

194
00:14:35,922 --> 00:14:36,946
That's true...

195
00:14:37,257 --> 00:14:39,384
I'll leave that to your own judgment.

196
00:14:40,460 --> 00:14:42,451
<i>I need to learn a trick again</i>
<i>to do this, don't I?</i>

197
00:14:43,530 --> 00:14:47,796
Well then,
I'll go gather some information.

198
00:14:47,868 --> 00:14:49,495
Hey! Wait, wait!

199
00:14:49,736 --> 00:14:52,034
Let's train together for
the first time in a while!

200
00:14:52,305 --> 00:14:53,863
I don't mind if you take a nap.

201
00:14:53,940 --> 00:14:55,305
Don't depend on me!

202
00:14:56,476 --> 00:14:59,240
You must have some kind
of misunderstanding!

203
00:15:00,780 --> 00:15:02,975
I did say that I'll teach you the Jutsu,

204
00:15:03,183 --> 00:15:05,378
but I don't have the obligation
to teach you every step of the way.

205
00:15:05,886 --> 00:15:07,786
If you can't do it by yourself,
then that's it.

206
00:15:08,889 --> 00:15:13,223
Don't be childish forever...
Become more respectable like a Shinobi!

207
00:15:13,426 --> 00:15:15,519
Well, well then.

208
00:15:15,729 --> 00:15:20,098
If you can at least teach me...
the trick again...

209
00:15:21,701 --> 00:15:22,429
Money!

210
00:15:22,636 --> 00:15:25,503
Money... money... money...

211
00:15:27,307 --> 00:15:30,242
W-What do you mean
"be respectable like a Shinobi"?!

212
00:15:30,443 --> 00:15:32,968
Even though you say that,
you're an dirty and greedy adult!

213
00:15:33,046 --> 00:15:35,514
You're not a respectable Shinobi at all!

214
00:15:49,529 --> 00:15:53,556
<i>It's way more difficult than</i>
<i>the time with the water balloon...</i>

215
00:15:55,802 --> 00:15:57,667
<i>A-And...</i>

216
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:02,470
<i>my hands and arms hurt.</i>

217
00:16:30,303 --> 00:16:34,103
Dang it! How many days am I
going to be doing the same thing!

218
00:16:42,215 --> 00:16:44,979
<i>Second from the top in</i>
<i>the difficulty of mastering...</i>

219
00:16:46,753 --> 00:16:48,015
<i>Don't depend on me!</i>

220
00:16:48,121 --> 00:16:50,646
<i>You must have some kind</i>
<i>of misunderstanding!</i>

221
00:16:51,124 --> 00:16:52,250
Dang it!

222
00:16:55,929 --> 00:16:57,294
Hey, Naruto.

223
00:16:57,998 --> 00:16:59,727
What did you come here for?

224
00:16:59,899 --> 00:17:02,231
Go buy some food from the town below.

225
00:17:02,402 --> 00:17:04,632
What?! Why me?

226
00:17:04,804 --> 00:17:05,828
Hey you...

227
00:17:05,905 --> 00:17:09,068
Even if for a while, you're still
learning the Jutsu from me.

228
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:15,609
Here you go, thanks for waiting

229
00:17:15,782 --> 00:17:17,181
Thank you.

230
00:17:19,919 --> 00:17:22,183
<i>How dare he put on a master's face</i>
<i>only at a time like this</i>

231
00:17:22,255 --> 00:17:24,746
<i>when he doesn't teach me anything...</i>

232
00:17:25,358 --> 00:17:27,417
Dad, buy me some ice cream.

233
00:17:28,328 --> 00:17:30,523
I want this one that cracks.

234
00:17:35,168 --> 00:17:35,862
Here.

235
00:17:35,969 --> 00:17:39,427
Why? I can eat all of it by myself.

236
00:17:40,006 --> 00:17:44,670
Nope, when you get home,
your mother will have supper ready.

237
00:17:44,944 --> 00:17:45,774
Okay!

238
00:17:51,584 --> 00:17:53,211
Hey... you know...

239
00:17:53,319 --> 00:17:54,149
Huh?

240
00:17:54,354 --> 00:17:59,087
Can you be around my training
for just a while... today?

241
00:17:59,426 --> 00:18:01,451
I don't have time for that.

242
00:18:01,861 --> 00:18:04,455
I have to immediately go to town.

243
00:18:06,866 --> 00:18:10,324
Unless you think for yourself and
get a grip of the trick for yourself,

244
00:18:10,403 --> 00:18:13,133
it'll never work.

245
00:18:14,607 --> 00:18:16,802
I thought I told you three weeks ago!

246
00:18:17,343 --> 00:18:21,677
Don't be spoiled like a kid.
You are a Ninja.

247
00:18:28,488 --> 00:18:31,082
I know that without
your telling me!

248
00:18:31,558 --> 00:18:33,958
Just thought I'd ask.

249
00:18:34,227 --> 00:18:36,855
Hurry up and go,
you Pervy Sage!

250
00:18:37,163 --> 00:18:40,155
Oh no, little Jiraiya,
you tell so many lies!

251
00:18:40,633 --> 00:18:43,568
What do you mean?!
Everything is true!

252
00:19:09,963 --> 00:19:13,592
Dang it! It doesn't break
no matter how much I try...

253
00:19:14,601 --> 00:19:18,298
I'm just dripping away
my Chakra this way.

254
00:19:20,507 --> 00:19:21,474
<i>Also...</i>

255
00:19:22,475 --> 00:19:26,206
<i>The more I increase the amount of flow,</i>
<i>the worse the pain gets.</i>

256
00:19:27,347 --> 00:19:29,577
<i>But... How do I say it?</i>

257
00:19:29,649 --> 00:19:32,277
<i>If I don't go all out as if</i>
<i>to explode the Chakra,</i>

258
00:19:32,352 --> 00:19:33,944
<i>it's not going to break!</i>

259
00:19:40,126 --> 00:19:40,888
<i>That's it!</i>

260
00:19:41,928 --> 00:19:44,396
<i>If I understand the amount of Chakra</i>
<i>that flows from the pain I feel...</i>

261
00:19:44,464 --> 00:19:48,594
<i>Then I can bear the pain to the limit</i>
<i>and all at once...</i>

262
00:19:50,637 --> 00:19:52,502
<i>No, not yet...</i>

263
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:54,938
<i>Not yet!</i>

264
00:19:59,045 --> 00:20:00,979
<i>Not yet...store it!</i>

265
00:20:04,984 --> 00:20:05,712
<i>Now!</i>

266
00:20:08,755 --> 00:20:10,279
Oww!

267
00:20:20,266 --> 00:20:23,360
Hmm... There seems to have been
a little progress.

268
00:20:24,437 --> 00:20:25,199
Humph!

269
00:20:25,271 --> 00:20:28,172
I've still only opened a hole
and it hasn't popped with a bang!

270
00:20:28,474 --> 00:20:31,739
Hey, don't pretend to be so tough. Here!

271
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:36,812
You've done well,
all on your own power.

272
00:20:43,456 --> 00:20:44,354
It's so good!

273
00:20:45,058 --> 00:20:46,025
Yes...

274
00:20:48,127 --> 00:20:50,425
Oh yeah. Maybe we'll test a bit.

275
00:20:51,397 --> 00:20:52,591
What, what?

276
00:20:52,999 --> 00:20:54,557
Give me your right hand.

277
00:21:03,576 --> 00:21:04,873
What's this?

278
00:21:09,617 --> 00:21:13,553
<i>A cycle of hardship, right?</i>

279
00:21:14,555 --> 00:21:18,514
<i>Inside, we were crying, right?</i>

280
00:21:19,827 --> 00:21:27,791
<i>But the one thing we won't give up</i>
<i>is the dream we've chosen, right?</i>

281
00:21:28,769 --> 00:21:30,862
<i>It's a secondary role,</i>

282
00:21:33,641 --> 00:21:36,667
<i>a role in the shadows</i>

283
00:21:37,111 --> 00:21:42,048
<i>But in reaching for that dream,</i>

284
00:21:42,183 --> 00:21:47,644
<i>let us stay centered,</i>
<i>let us stay true</i>

285
00:21:47,822 --> 00:21:52,725
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we hung on without giving up</i>

286
00:21:52,793 --> 00:21:57,696
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we kept coming back up</i>

287
00:21:57,765 --> 00:22:06,935
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we believed and dreamed</i>

288
00:22:07,408 --> 00:22:12,277
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we've seen fools</i>

289
00:22:12,346 --> 00:22:18,182
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we've stood in the shadows of others</i>

290
00:22:19,820 --> 00:22:29,957
<i>Now, it's our turn...</i>
<i>Let us bask in our dreams</i>

291
00:22:37,939 --> 00:22:40,032
He tells me
"focus, focus, focus!"

292
00:22:40,308 --> 00:22:43,072
But I've never been good at it, ever.

293
00:22:44,812 --> 00:22:46,712
Speaking of concentration,

294
00:22:46,781 --> 00:22:50,717
Iruka Sensei used to scold me often
at the Ninja Academy

295
00:22:50,785 --> 00:22:52,412
for my lack of concentration.

296
00:22:52,954 --> 00:22:58,415
Oh... I would've listened to him better
if I knew this would happen.

297
00:22:59,393 --> 00:23:02,658
Next time: "Focal Point:
The Mark of the Leaf"
